              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The pulse distribution of the C6-D6 detectors were",
                " calibrated regularly during the experiment using the",
                " radioactive sources Cs-137, Co-602 and a composite",
                " source of the alpha-emitter Pu-238 and carbon, giving",
                " a 6.13-MeV gamma-rays through the C-13(alpha,n)O-16",
                " reaction.",
                ".After correction for background, the capture yield can",
                " be determined from the weighted count rate spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Two disc-shaped thorium samples with a diameter of",
                " 1.5 mm, total mass of 2.8037 g and a purity of 99.5%",
                " were used.",
                " Metallic gold samples, 1.33 g thick-verify",
                " the analysis procedure and of natural lead, 2.04 g",
                " thick-estimate the background due to in beam photons",
                " scattered from the sample. All samples were 15 mm in",
                " diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Correction for the attenuation of the in-beam",
                " gamma-rays was made by the filters 30 mm thick",
                " Aluminum neutron black resonance filter.",
                ".Correction for self-absorption and multiple-scatte-",
                " ring effects."
              ]
            }
          ],
